datstructure

Class Entry

  • java.lang.Object
    • datstructure.Entry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Entry>, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Object>

    public class Entry
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Entry>, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Object>
    An Entry is an object in the file. It contains a sequence of values which must be read from the file in a given order (the datStructure object) An entry usually define a Name, a Sequence Number and an ID (sometimes it doesn't define one or more of them). Undefined/Unused fields usually have a negative ID and sequence number. Sometimes there's an undefined field used as "null" element by other objects and must not be altered.
    Author:
    MarcoForlini
